Max Muggeridge , 19, from the Gold Coast caught a four metre tiger shark at the weekend . 
  He was camping on the Tweed coast just inside the NSW border . 
  He reeled in the monster after a three hour battle with the beast . 
  The teenager said it was one of the largest tiger sharks ever caught off a beach . 
  He believes it could have been close to the world record size . 
  He said he was camping at Tweed Heads with his girlfriend . 
